2 HOUSE BILL 1257
1 Article – Education
2 5–101.
3 (a) (1) Subject to the rules and regulations of the State Board and with the
4 advice of the county superintendent, each county board shall prepare an annual budget
5 according to:
6 (i) The major categories listed in this section; and
7 (ii) Any other major category required by the State Board.
8 (2) In addition to the information required by this section, the county fiscal
9 authorities may require the county board to provide details to the service areas and
10 activities levels in the account structure within the “Financial Reporting Manual for
11 Maryland Public Schools”.
12 (3) With the annual budget, each county board shall provide:
13 (i) The number of full–time equivalent positions included within
14 each major category; and
15 (ii) A description of any fund balances or other money held by any
16 outside source, including an insurer, that are undesignated or unreserved and are under
17 the direction and control of the county board.
18 (4) The State Board shall adopt a process for the uniform reporting of the
19 information in subsection (b) of this section to timely share the information provided by a
20 county board in subsection (b) of this section to a county governing body.
21 (b) The budget shall be prepared to include the following categories:
22 Part I
23 (1) Current expense fund, estimated receipts:
24 (i) Revenue from local sources;
25 (ii) Revenue from State sources;
26 (iii) Revenue from federal sources;
27 (iv) Unliquidated surplus, the actual from the previous fiscal year
28 and the estimated from the current fiscal year, whether accrued from revenues or
29 expenditures; and
30 (v) Revenue from all other sources with identification of the source.

HOUSE BILL 1257 3
1 (2) Current expense fund, requested appropriations:
2 (i) Administration, which means those activities associated with the
3 general regulations, direction, and control of the county board, including:
4 1. Executive administration;
5 2. Business support services; and
6 3. Centralized support services;
7 (ii) Mid–level administration, including:
8 1. The office of the school principal; and
9 2. Staff providing administration and supervision to the
10 school instructional programs;
11 (iii) Instructional salaries, which means those activities which deal
12 directly with teaching students, including:
13 1. Teachers;
14 2. Aides;
15 3. Psychological personnel;
16 4. Guidance counselors; and
17 5. Library personnel;
18 (iv) Textbooks and classroom instructional supplies;
19 (v) Other instructional costs;
20 (vi) Special education with subcategories and items budgeted in this
21 category to be determined by the State Board with the advice of the county board;
22 (vii) Student personnel services;
23 (viii) Health services;
24 (ix) Student transportation;
25 (x) Operation of plant and equipment;

4 HOUSE BILL 1257
1 (xi) Maintenance of plant;
2 (xii) Fixed charges;
3 (xiii) Food services; and
4 (xiv) Capital outlay.
5 (3) Current funds held in reserve, including:
6 (i) Revenue to and expenditures from funds held in reserve in the
7 prior fiscal year; and
8 (ii) Appropriations planned in the upcoming fiscal year from funds
9 held in reserve.
10 (4) The amount of any federal funds received in the last fiscal year,
11 including:
12 (i) Expenditures of the federal funds in the prior fiscal year;
13 (ii) A description of whether the federal funds are committed for a
14 particular purpose; and
15 (iii) The anticipated timing to appropriate the federal funds in the
16 upcoming fiscal year.
17 (5) The amount of funds held in trust or otherwise dedicated toward
18 long–term obligations for retiree health care costs or other postemployment benefits, and
19 information used to calculate the county board’s obligation for those costs.
20 Part II
21 (6) School construction fund, estimated receipts:
22 (i) Revenue from local sources;
23 (ii) Sale of bonds;
24 (iii) State General Public School Construction Loan;
25 (iv) Revenue from State sources;
26 (v) Revenue from federal sources;

HOUSE BILL 1257 5
1 (vi) Unliquidated surplus, the actual from the previous fiscal year
2 and the estimated for the current fiscal year, whether accrued from revenues or
3 expenditures; and
4 (vii) Funds from all other sources, with identification of the source.
5 (7) School Construction Fund, requested appropriations:
6 (i) Land for school sites;
7 (ii) Buildings and the equipment that will be an integral part of a
8 building by project;
9 (iii) School site improvement by project;
10 (iv) Remodeling by project;
11 (v) Additional equipment by project;
12 (vi) Debt service; and
13 (vii) An amount that is adequate to satisfy a final court judgment
14 that, after exhaustion of the rights of appeal, is rendered against the county board of
15 education or any of its officers or employees.
16 (G) (1) IN ADDITION TO ALL OTHER INFORMATION REQUIRED UNDER
17 THIS SECTION, THE BALTIMORE COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION SHALL PROVIDE
18 TO THE BALTIMORE COUNTY EXECUTIVE AND BALTIMORE COUNTY COUNCIL, WITH
19 THE ANNUAL BUDGET, INFORMATION RELATING TO EACH OF THE FOLLOWING:
20 (I) PERSONNEL DATA WITH FULL–TIME EQUIVALENT
21 POSITIONS BY JOB TITLE AND DEPARTMENT; AND
22 (II) EXPENDITURES DISAGGREGATED BY THE CATEGORIES
23 SPECIFIED IN SUBSECTION (B)(2) OF THIS SECTION.
24 (2) THE BALTIMORE COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION SHALL
25 PROVIDE, IN A PUBLICLY AVAILABLE ONLINE FORMAT, THE FOLLOWING
26 INFORMATION:
27 (I) HISTORICAL BUDGET DATA, VENDOR CONTRACT AWARDS,
28 AND SCHOOL–LEVEL ENROLLMENT DATA;
29 (1) (I) HISTORICAL BUDGET DATA FROM THE THREE PREVIOUS
30 FISCAL YEARS;

6 HOUSE BILL 1257
1 (II) VENDOR CONTRACT AWARDS FOR THE CURRENT FISCAL
2 YEAR AND THE PREVIOUS FISCAL YEAR; AND
3 (III) SCHOOL–LEVEL ENROLLMENT DATA FOR THE CURRENT
4 FISCAL YEAR;
5 (II) (2) QUARTERLY REPORTS WITH CURRENT MONTHLY
6 EXPENDITURES COMPARED TO THE ANNUAL BUDGET; AND
7 (III) (3) THE STATUS OF ALL CAPITAL IMPROVEMENT
8 PROJECTS, CURRENT SPENDING, AND PROJECTED COMPLETION DATES.
9 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
10 1, 2026.
